 Prevention of Food Adulteration Rules, 1955: Rules 44(g) and 47 (As amended by Prevention of Food Adulteration (Third Amendment) Rules, 1968 and as they stood prior to Amendment of 15.4.1988)--,Appendix 'B'---Restriction on sale of Articles containing/Irtificial sweetener/ Saccharin--Prescription of standard of saccharin or any artificial sweetener in Appendix 'B' is not relevant-Stand- ard must be prescribed in respect of Article of sale--Stand- ard must permit user of sweetener in the Article--No stand- ard laid down for Supari and Pan Masala--Held addition of artificial sweetener saccharin in Pan Masala and Supari is prohibited.
 
